# Program Design Document

## Program Name

Project 1 Gpa Calculator. 

## Purpose

So the following program allows the user to input credit values and letter grades of classes taken, these values are specfic to a singular class, in which the user is able to continue adding the class, credits, and letter grade. Calculating the total final gpa.  

---

## Inputs

The program receives the following inputs from the user:

Credits for each class
Letter grade for each class
Whether the user wants to enter another class, using Y or N

Valid grades include:

A+, A, A-, B+, B, B-, C+, C, D, F, WU, FIN, FAB

Valid credits must be greater than 0 and less than 10.


---

## Outputs

Instructions for how to use the GPA calculator

Invalid input messages when credits or grades are not valid

The number of classes entered

The final semester GPA

A message saying no classes were entered if the user does not enter any valid classes.

---

## Variables

| Variable | Type   | Purpose                   |
| -------- | ------ | ------------------------- |
| tc    | double |Stores the total number of credits entered       |
| tp  | double | Stores total points earned from all classes inputed.  |
| credits  | double |Stores the credit value for the current class.      |
| Gradepoints  | double |Stores the number value of the letter grade, such as A = 4.0 or B = 3.0. |
| grade    | string   | Stores letter grade       |
|classesTaken | int | Stores how many valid classes the user entered.
|again | char | Stores whether the user wants to enter another class.
