## Key Design Choices

Explain any important decisions you made when designing the program.

I impleted a loop into my code when asking for the classes as the project requirments require multiple classes, thier letter grade and credits. Not using this would have made me write endless amounts of code accomadating this user input. 

I also used an upper case mechanic in which if user inputs any lowe case letter it is automatically turned into an upper case to make the code insensitive to upper or lower case letters. For example, if the user enters a or b+, the program changes it to A or B+. This makes the program easier to implement the case insensitive requirement. 

I chose to use if and if else statments instead of switch as some of the letter grades have more than one characters. 


---

## Program Steps (Algorithm)

1. Prompts user on how to use program, asking to ender credits from 0.1-9.9 followed by the grade for one class. 
2. Validates the users input, if invalid outputs error based on range of 0 to less than 10. 
3. Converts any letter input to upper case. 
4. Stores information entered. (via adding to variables, tp, tc and classes taken)
5. asks the user if they want to keep going via y/n.
6. if any parts invalid lets user know and asks for another input. 
7. Determine/perform calculations results.
8. Displays output of culamtive gpa, and classes taken. 

